 tell the DMV the insurance had been cancelled, even though they already tell any lienholders].<br>
<br>
Thankfully, I'm insured and pay extra to have uninsured motorist coverage to protect me from assholes like her.  It's part of the privilege of driving in CA.  Rather than forcing others to be responsible for you, we require you to do so.  No, we aren't idiots and are simply going to trust that you'll do the right thing.  Just like the cow that hit me, people will frequently cancel their insurance.  22% of drivers on the road aren't insured, even after the law requiring you to be insured.<br>
<br>
Lixivia:  Good to see ya ol' guildie [remember me from Sentries of Faith?].  Here's how insurance works:  50 people all agree to pay Allstate a certain amount of money.  Allstate then holds the groups' money aside in case one of them gets into an accident.  The amount that each of the 50 pay will be less than what it cost the one that got into the accident to get back to their original condition (car repairs, hospital bills, trips to Cancun, whatever).  <br>
<br>
Now the amount each of the 50 people pay will vary depending upon relevant statistics that determine the risks to Allstate that one of them will get into an accident.  Driving record, age, sex, residence, type of car, etc.  With the millions of drivers in the US and elsewhere, the insurance companies have pretty good ideas about what factors increase the risk of an incident.<br>
<br>
I hope that helps clear some of it up. <p>-- The <select><option>SOB</option><option>Grump</option><option>Bastard</option><option>pwner of Chiteng</option></select> formerly known as Raedwulf</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/unekiahdragonsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nekiah Dragonsbane</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 918<br> <font color=#E9D756>(10/10/02 7:18:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3712.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: insurance</span><hr size=1> Insurance companies are truly evil incarnate.<br>
