Careful Gurglespit. Laws exacted upon insurers are pretty much state specific in the US and widely vary between countries.<br>
<br>
I was an insurance agent for "Farmers Insurance" for 4 years in the state of Washington (USA) and we <i><b>were not</i></b> required by law to explain everything the customer didn't understand.<br>
<br>
It is buyer beware for the most part. Even if you the customer believes that everything is being explained to you it probably isn't. We don't usually find out until we have a claim that our rear ends are now raw.<br>
