 <p>Gurg V1.0</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uraedwulf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raedwulf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1508<br> <font color=#E9D756>(10/11/02 10:47:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3712.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: insurance</span><hr size=1> I believe Lurikeen is right that there is no obligation to explain all of the provisions of an insurance policy to the prospective insured, at least in California.  I've defended insurance agents in Professional Negligence cases, and they did not have a duty to explain every aspect of a policy.  It's a good business practice to do so and usually avoids litigation down the line, but it's not required.  If you sign a contract, you are under an obligation to have read and understood it before you did so.  Even though some provisions may be difficult to understand, even by someone who reads lots of insurance policies like me, the insured is still deemed to have read and understood the policy when purchased.  You snooze, you lose.<br>
<br>
Now, that does not give the agent the right to mislead the consumer regarding the scope of coverage and other bullspit that is being ordered.  And many good insurers will have their own rules requiring full disclosure and explanation. <p>-- The <select><option>SOB</option><option>Grump</option><option>Bastard</option><option>pwner of Chiteng</option></select> formerly known as Raedwulf</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ugurglespitfruggybasher.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gurglespit Fruggybasher</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://dyce.i8.com/gurblip.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1527<br> <font color=#E9D756>(10/11/02 11:35:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3712.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: insurance</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I believe Lurikeen is right that there is no obligation to explain all of the provisions of an insurance policy to the prospective insured, at least in California. I've defended insurance agents in Professional Negligence cases, and they did not have a duty to explain every aspect of a policy. It's a good business practice to do so and usually avoids litigation down the line, but it's not required. If you sign a contract, you are under an obligation to have read and understood it before you did so. Even though some provisions may be difficult to understand, even by someone who reads lots of insurance policies like me, the insured is still deemed to have read and understood the policy when purchased. You snooze, you lose.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I'm not saying that agents are required to tell every person about every aspect of thier policy.. I am saying that if the person asks a question about something they don't understand about thier policy or prospective policy, the agent is obligated to explain whatever you asked about.  If you don't ask about something, then don't expect to have it explained to you. Therefore, if you don't understand anything about your policy, then ask, and they should tell you. <p>Gurg V1.0</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uraedwulf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raedwulf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1509<br> <font color=#E9D756>(10/11/02 11:45:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3712.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: insurance</span><hr size=1> I agree. <p>-- The <select><option>SOB</option><option>Grump</option><option>Bastard</option><option>pwner of Chiteng</option></select> formerly known as Raedwulf</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showPrevMessage?topicID=3712.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showNextMessage?topicID=3712.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3712.topic&index=14><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandpl